def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Extract the data index and its levels and codes
    index = data.index
    levels = index.levels
    codes = index.codes
    names = index.names

    # Identify the levels and codes for columns to be unstacked
    cloc_levels = [levels[i] for i in clocs]
    cloc_codes = [codes[i] for i in clocs]
    cloc_names = [names[i] for i in clocs]

    # Remove the clocs from the original levels and codes
    rloc_levels = [level for i, level in enumerate(levels) if i not in clocs]
    rloc_codes = [code for i, code in enumerate(codes) if i not in clocs]
    rloc_names = [name for i, name in enumerate(names) if i not in clocs]

    # Unstack the data
    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    new_columns = pd.MultiIndex.from_product(cloc_levels, names=cloc_names)
    new_columns.codes = pd.MultiIndex.from_product(cloc_codes, names=cloc_names)
    unstacked.columns = new_columns

    return unstacked
